Package: alsi
Type: Package
Title: Aggregated Latent Space Index: Stability-Validated Aggregation
    across Binary, Ordinal, and Continuous Data
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-03-19
Authors@R: person("Se-Kang", "Kim",
    email = "se-kang.kim@bcm.edu",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0928-3396"))
Description: Implements stability-validated workflows for constructing a
    person-level scalar index — the Aggregated Latent Space Index (ALSI) —
    that summarizes multidimensional association structure across binary,
    ordinal Likert-type, and continuous multivariate data. For binary data,
    ALSI is a variance-weighted L2 norm of row principal coordinates from
    multiple correspondence analysis (MCA). For ordinal data, ALSI is an
    eigenvalue-weighted composite of person scores from homals alternating
    least squares (ALS) optimal scaling. For continuous data, the continuous
    ALSI (cALSI) is derived from ipsatized singular value decomposition
    (SVD), isolating within-person profile shape. Across all three pipelines,
    dimensionality is assessed via parallel analysis and subspace stability
    via bootstrap Procrustes alignment using principal angles and Tucker
    congruence coefficients; only stable dimensions are retained. Automated
    workflow functions, visualization tools, and consistent S3 return
    structures are provided for all three data types.
